Mî-li-kiên Ha̍p-chung-koet ({{ngî+en|United States of America}}) thûng-sòng chhṳ̂n-cho Mî-koet ({{ngî-en|America}}), he vi-yî [[Pet-mî-chû|Pet-Mî-chû]] ke lièn-pâng khiung-fò chṳ koet-kâ, ya-he sṳ-kie sông chui yû-kiú ke koet-kâ. Mî-koet pún-thú hiong-tûng he [[Thai-sî-yòng]], sî-lìm [[Thai-phìn-yòng]], pet piên-kie kho-chho̍k [[Kâ-nâ-thai]], nàm-fông chiap [[Me̍t-sî-kô]] khi̍p Me̍t-sî-kô vân. Sú-tû he [[Fà-sṳn-tun]] Kô-lùn-pí-â thi̍t-khî. Mî-koet ngièn chhṳ chhut-yì [[1776-ngièn]] thot-lì [[Yîn-koet]] thúng-chhṳ ke Pet-Mî chhṳ̍t-mìn-thi, Sṳ̍p-sâm chû ke chhṳ̍t-mìn-thi thoi-péu yit-thùng fat-péu liáu "[[Mî-koet Thu̍k-li̍p Siên-ngièn]]", chhai kîn-li̍t kiên-khú ke thu̍k-li̍p chan-chên heu, yî [[1783-ngièn]] lâu Yîn-koet chhiâm-thin Pâ-lì hia̍p-yok, chhiùng-chhṳ́ su-tó sṳ-kie kok-koet ke sṳ̀n-ngin.

